		<div class="commententry" id="commententry-102166">
					
			<p>I agree with Darren, this is a major problem since the entire point is to support mobile browsers.  It would be good to update this article with a solution, but I don&#8217;t think there exists a css based solution to this problem.  I am not sure about other mobile devices, but IOS supports the :hover by actually showing the hidden element and then performing a click.  Presumably this was implemented by Apple to help make non-mobile sites more friendly.</p>

